ABUJA – Mr. Isa Abdulmumin, has been appointed as the Acting Director of Corporate Communications Department of the Central Bank. He takes over from Osita Nwanisobi as head of the Corporate Communications Department following his (Nwanisobi’s) retirement from service on Friday. Abdulmumin, a deputy director, has been in the Corporate Communications Department of the CBN since he joined the bank. He is seen as a thoroughbred professional who enjoys the goodwill and cooperation of his colleagues in the department, bank, media and corporate society at large. Osita Nwanisobi took over from Isaac Okorafor in 2020, and before then, was a Special Assistant to the Deputy Governor, Financial System Stability (FSS), between 2009 and 2011. By Felix Ugboja ABUJA (Sundiata Post)  - A Member of House of Representatives, Honourable Abdulmumin Jibrin, has reacted to President Buhari's Monday speech after returning from London, saying that he did not expect the President to have read his speech like a coup d’etat. Abdulmumin stated this on his twitter… In "Top Stories" - Suspended member of the House of Representatives, Abdulmumin Jibrin, has revealed that some politicians have started questioning the authority of the Acting President, Yemi Osinbajo - He said that there may be cracks in the government if “some people” start questioning Osinbajo’s orders as Acting President - He also… In "News" The National Identity Management Commission (NIMC) has so far registered 1.2 million Nigerians into the National Identity Database and has issued them with the National Identification Number (NIN) in Bauchi. Malam Isa Abdulmumin, NIMC Bauchi state coordinator, made this known in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria NAN… In "News"